      • deepFeatures

        public static <T extends com.ekito.simpleKML.model.Feature> void deepFeatures​(com.ekito.simpleKML.model.Kml kml,
                                                                              FeatureHandler<T> handler,
                                                                              java.lang.Class<T> clazz)
        Get all matching features of the specified type Recurse Document and all Folders Similar to MapGroup.deepForEachItem pattern If handler returns true for any feature, processing stops. You may use this if have already found the feature you are looking for, or you just want the first feature we happen to find We support this pattern for better performance on KML files with large numbers of Placemarks
        Parameters:
        kml - the kml object to search
        clazz -

      • convertKmlCoord

        public static com.ekito.simpleKML.model.Coordinate convertKmlCoord​(GeoPointMetaData point,
                                                                   boolean excludeAltitude,
                                                                   double unwrap)
        Convert a geopoint with height into a KML Coordinate. With KML, the representation is the top of the item so the altitude used is actually the altitude + height which differs from TAK where the altitude is the bottom and the height is relative to the altitude.
        Parameters:
        point - the point to use for the latitude, longitude, and altitude.
        excludeAltitude - the boolean to exclude the altitude from the kml string
        unwrap - if the idl wrap is to be applied
        Returns:
        the KML Coordinate
